 didn't work as relyable as I would wish it. Maybe I’m simply to clumsy?<P>2.) The already spoken options in the dialogues should be removed. Due to the fact that everyone's able to read the old sentences in the diary this would permit a very fast overview wether there are new dialogue-options or not.<P>(for example you could still choose the sentence that you'd found a possibility to rescue both soldiers after you had healed them already long time ago).<P>3.) A right-click into an inventory-window should close this special one.<P>4.) Left-double-click on a item should generally move it into the inventory and a right-click (or a key in combination with the left-click or a click with the third mousekey) should utilize the item.<P>The momentary mixture is not optimal (sometimes a left-double-click leads to doing something with the item and another item goes straight to the inventory after double-click with the left mousekey, nobody knows when. And as this wouldn’t be enough, some items have to be drawn to the inventory)<P>5.) It shouldn’t be allowed to use the teleporting pyramid-stone during a battle! At the moment the healing potions are only usefull to bring money by the trader because I don’t use them. If there are many enemies (or a very strong single one) I use the pyramid-stone to jump directly to my bed, rest for a while and then jump back to the battle, give some hits to the monsters and jump back and so on and so on.<BR>In the momentary constellation he is to mighty.<P>6.) Special items should be found every time at the same place!! It’s boring to beginn a complete new search after reloading a savegame.<P>7.) It’s strange when piles of gold are lying on the ground for a longer time (even in the forest). The NPCs should pick them after a while and it should be the same with valuable things, so that the player is forced to use empty barrels or cases (there are enough of them)<P>8.) The night lasts to long or other way round, the day is to short. That is the connection to the next point.<P>9.) Daylight should be much stronger (I had always the feeling it’s a rainy day) and in the opposite the night may be a little bit darker. Simple: The difference should be stronger.<P>10.) Again something with the light: Once you made the effort to stuff all the dungeons with torches or fire basins, why is there still light left, when you douse them?? That’S not logical and a pity about your work with the possibility to influence candles an torches.<P>11.) Consequently it should be much easier to steal something when it’s dark and the more harder when it’s well lit.<P><BR>That’s all I remember at the moment. I wish a good game for all of us!! (gamers and developers)<P>So long<BR>Ebi<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thank you for writing.<P>You could also post in the german-language-section of this Forum.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey Ebi, Some nice suggestions and some of them I REALLY like but I think that Huge changes won't be made anymore since the german version is going gold in 3 weeks. I think it's now the time for optimizing code and tweaking it for performance.<P>------------------<BR>"My precious"<BR><A HREF="http://users.pandora.be/hammes/DivineDivinity/index.html" TARGET=_blank>My Divine Divinity Fanpages</A><BR><A HREF="http://users.pandora.be/hammes" TARGET=_blank>Yo yo yo, Check this out</A> --&gt; anyone knowing the "supahfly" by Joecartoon will get this<BR>Second member of the <B>Guild of New People Welcomers and other druidic occupations</B></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD>